race.comment: Race has been completely turned on its head post scratchings with several key chances out. SWEET JUSTICE (14) shapes as the main beneficary. Mixed form however showed glimpses of promise during her first campaign which returned a maiden victory before running behind subsequent multiple Group 1 winner Treasurethe Moment. Resumed at Ballarat on September 19 with a fast closing third. Will be fitter for the run and rises in distance. Tends to get back so in a smaller field won't have to spot her rivals too much of a start. PRINCESS TORO (13) resumes. Campaign late last season returned a win at Ballarat. JUGIONG (7) showed good improvement second up when winning at Wodonga. Barring her first up run this campaign he has been a model of consistency in his short career to date. RUNAWAY SOUL (10) chasing a third straight victory next elect.
